The paper focuses on a machine learning-based approach for error detection, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and data management. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and weak supervision, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on various datasets, which may involve issues related to data privacy and security (cs.CR) and data management (cs.DB).
